HEADWORD: Bypath
<hw>By"path`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Bypaths</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>A private path; an obscure
way; indirect means.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God known, my son,⟦br⟧
By what <qex>bypaths</qex>, and indirect crooked ways,⟦br⟧
I met this crown.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>By-place</ent>⟦br⟧
